# Security & KVKK

This product is **healthcare-adjacent**. Treat as sensitive:

- Clinical/treatment notes and health-related text
- Messages and conversation content
- Phone numbers and personal identifiers

## Requirements

- Do **not** log sensitive data (notes, message bodies, phones) to console, error trackers, or audit logs beyond what policy allows
- Do **not** expose data across workspaces — enforce RLS + application-level tenant checks
- Never commit secrets (`.env`, API keys, tokens) — use env vars only
- Validate and sanitize all user input; scope queries by `workspace_id`
- Webhook endpoints: verify signatures, reject replay, enforce idempotency

## AI and automation

- No automatic medical advice to patients
- No automatic outbound messages without explicit human approval
- AI features (future): summaries/drafts only, human-in-the-loop

Reference: `docs/08-security-kvkk.md`, ADR-006 in `docs/DECISIONS.md`
